It's alleged that the bakkie was attempting to overtake another car when it collided with the taxi. JOHANNESBURG - Police said 9 people died and 27 others were injured in a car accident in Limpopo on Saturday evening. The accident happened near Rafiri Village in Zebediela when a bakkie crashed into a mini bus taxi. It's alleged that the bakkie was attempting to overtake another car when it collided with the taxi. Police spokesperson Moatshe Ngoepe said, “Police are investigating a case of culpable homicide.” (Edited by Refilwe Pitjeng)